Package: badcontrols
Title: Difference-in-Differences with Bad Controls
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Carolina", "Caetano", role = "aut",
           email = "ccaetano@uga.edu"),
    person("Brantly", "Callaway", role = "aut",
           email = "brantly.callaway@uga.edu"),
    person("Stroud", "Payne", role = "aut",
           email = "stroud.payne@vanderbilt.edu"),
    person("Hugo", "Sant'Anna", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "hsantanna@uab.edu")
    )
Description: Implements methods for difference-in-differences when
    time-varying covariates are affected by treatment (bad controls).
    Provides imputation-based and doubly robust machine learning estimators
    that correctly handle post-treatment covariates. Builds on the panel
    treatment effects infrastructure in 'pte'. Based on Caetano, Callaway,
    Payne, and Sant'Anna (2024) "Difference-in-Differences with Bad Controls".
URL: https://github.com/hsantanna88/bad-controls
